replies.body:
{{champion:112}} 

Viktor's one of the top-tier genuises of the current generation - focused on transcending the flesh of *all* mankind - not just that of Zaunites. He's running about with the intent of proving how awesome he is, and genuinely seems inclined to help others in that sort of zany "wanna be a robot?" kind of way that he's famous for.

Soooo.... y'know.

Anyone who's against Zaun, maybe? If Janna's a secondary for Piltover, then Ekko could be, too. Zac could perhaps be persuaded, as could Viktor. (...and anyone else Zaun has wronged.) Since Bandle City and Piltover have historically been allies, I think that all yordles not pledged elsewhere should be available pickups.
Now, leaving out all the Noxian and Shuriman champions, here are some that may work with a poke playstyle:
{{champion:43}} {{champion:96}} {{champion:76}} {{champion:37}} {{champion:134}} {{champion:161}} {{champion:143}} {{champion:99}}

Several ideas for champion picks

{{champion:13}} 
Ryze works better with Piltover than Shurima. He would want to stop Shurima from destroying their country again, and keep Noxus from getting powerful spells. He also has a hatred of Xerath, saying that he is an abomination and must be destroyed.

{{champion:161}} 
A darker path for Piltover. Trade for knowledge with the Void. Risky, but it could be rewarding.

{{champion:38}} 
If Shurima turns to the void he'll probably want to keep things from going to hell again. 

{{champion:79}} 
With Piltover needing champions he could join as a tertiary in exchange for some scientists to help him with his beer.

{{champion:68}} 
Rumble probably has some opinions on Piltover making a train to Bandle City. 

{{champion:236}} 
Lucian's guns are called relic weapons, but why would Demacia have relic guns. Perhaps the relics are of Piltoverian origins.

{{champion:11}} 
Master Yi's goggles are made by Heimerdinger.
